# app reads env from the repo root `.env` (see `package.json` build/dev scripts).
# Copy relevant keys into ../.env — do not commit real secrets.

# Vibe sandbox iframe — default is http://localhost:8081/sandbox.html (see `DEFAULT_SANDBOX_BASE` in `@avenos/vibe-app-sandbox`).
# When the sandbox listens on another port (`VIBE_SANDBOX_PORT` / `PORT` in root `.env`), set this to match:
# PUBLIC_VIBE_SANDBOX_URL=http://localhost:8082/sandbox.html

# SvelteKit dev (browser: `bun dev:app`, Tauri shell: `bun dev:app:macos`) listens on http://127.0.0.1:1420 by default (see `app/vite.config.ts`).

# Cartesi webcm (RISC-V Linux WASM) served from `app/static/webcm/` — run `bun run fetch:webcm` once after clone.
# PUBLIC_WEBCM_BASE=/webcm

# AvenOS Hyperswarm env vars belong on the **Tauri app process** — see ../.env.example (P2P section).
